<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>PlaceOS CampusOS — Proposal for <%= quote.company_name %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@0.309.0/dist/umd/lucide.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Limited Time Offer Banner -->
<% if (quote.status === 'pending') {
  const createdDate = new Date(quote.created_at);
  const expiryDate = new Date(createdDate.getTime() + 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
  const earlyBirdDate = new Date(createdDate.getTime() + 3 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
%>
<div class="limited-offer-banner" id="offerBanner">
  <div class="container" style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:16px;">
    <div style="flex:1;">
      <div class="banner-label">Limited Time Offer</div>
      <div class="banner-text">Sign within 72 hours & receive <strong>$2,000 implementation credit</strong></div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:20px;">
      <div id="countdown" style="display:flex; gap:8px; font-weight:600; font-size:0.95em;"></div>
      <a href="#acceptSection" class="banner-cta">Sign Now</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<% } %>

<!-- Header -->
<div class="proposal-header">
  <div class="logo">Place<span>OS</span></div>
  <h1>CampusOS Proposal</h1>
  <div class="company"><%= quote.company_name %></div>
  <div class="date">
    Prepared for <strong><%= quote.contact_name %></strong> &middot; <%= new Date(quote.created_at).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year:'numeric', month:'long', day:'numeric' }) %>
  </div>
  <% if (quote.status === 'accepted') { %>
    <div class="proposal-badge badge-accepted">Accepted</div>
  <% } else { %>
    <div class="proposal-badge badge-pending">Offer Expires in 7 Days</div>
  <% } %>
</div>

<div class="proposal-body">

  <!-- Executive Summary -->
  <div class="proposal-card">
    <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
    <p>PlaceOS CampusOS is a comprehensive smart campus management platform that transforms how <strong><%= quote.company_name %></strong> manages its campus environment. From bookable spaces and AV control to visitor management and environmental monitoring, CampusOS provides a unified, intelligent layer across your entire campus.</p>
    <p>This proposal covers an annual software licence for your configured campus of <strong><%= quote.num_bookable_spaces %> bookable spaces</strong>, <strong><%= quote.num_floors %> floors</strong><% if (quote.num_parking_spaces > 0) { %>, <strong><%= quote.num_parking_spaces %> parking spaces</strong><% } %><% if (quote.num_av_rooms > 0) { %>, <strong><%= quote.num_av_rooms %> AV rooms</strong><% } %> across <strong><%= quote.num_buildings %> building(s)</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Features Included -->
  <div class="proposal-card">
    <h2>What's Included</h2>
    <div class="features-included">
      <% if (quote.num_bookable_spaces > 0) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="calendar-range"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Bookable Spaces</h4><p>Intelligent scheduling for lecture halls, seminar rooms, labs, libraries, and collaborative zones with real-time availability.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (quote.num_floors > 0) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="bar-chart-3"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Space Utilisation</h4><p>Real-time occupancy analytics, heatmaps, and utilisation dashboards powered by sensor data across campus.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="thermometer"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Environmental Monitoring</h4><p>Track temperature, humidity, CO2, and air quality across every floor for comfort and compliance.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (quote.num_parking_spaces > 0) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="car"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Campus Parking</h4><p>Automated parking allocation and booking for staff and students via mobile app.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (quote.num_av_rooms > 0) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="speaker"></i></div>
        <div><h4>AV Control</h4><p>Automated AV management for lecture theatres — projectors, screens, microphones, and recording systems.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (quote.include_digital_signage) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="monitor"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Digital Signage</h4><p>Campus wayfinding, room schedules, event announcements, and real-time information displays.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (quote.include_visitor_mgmt) { %>
      <div class="feature-item">
        <div class="fi-icon"><i data-lucide="user-check"></i></div>
        <div><h4>Visitor Management</h4><p>Guest check-in, event registration, campus tours, host notifications, and compliance tracking.</p></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Pricing Breakdown -->
  <div class="proposal-card">
    <h2>Annual Licence Pricing</h2>
    <p style="color:#888; font-size:0.9em; margin-bottom:16px;">All pricing in USD, per annum, excluding GST.</p>
    <table class="price-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Quantity</th><th>Unit Price</th><th>Annual Total</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <% if (quote.num_bookable_spaces > 0) { %>
        <tr><td>Bookable Spaces</td><td><%= quote.num_bookable_spaces %> spaces</td><td>$<%= PRICING.bookable_spaces.usd %>/space</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_bookable_spaces * PRICING.bookable_spaces.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <% if (quote.num_floors > 0) { %>
        <tr><td>Environmental Monitoring</td><td><%= quote.num_floors %> floors</td><td>$<%= PRICING.env_monitoring.usd.toLocaleString() %>/floor</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_floors * PRICING.env_monitoring.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Space Utilisation</td><td><%= quote.num_floors %> floors</td><td>$<%= PRICING.space_util.usd.toLocaleString() %>/floor</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_floors * PRICING.space_util.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <% if (quote.num_parking_spaces > 0) { %>
        <tr><td>Campus Parking</td><td><%= quote.num_parking_spaces %> spaces</td><td>$<%= PRICING.campus_parking.usd %>/space</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_parking_spaces * PRICING.campus_parking.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <% if (quote.num_av_rooms > 0) { %>
        <tr><td>AV Control</td><td><%= quote.num_av_rooms %> rooms</td><td>$<%= PRICING.av_control.usd %>/room</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_av_rooms * PRICING.av_control.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <% if (quote.include_digital_signage) { %>
        <tr><td>Digital Signage</td><td><%= quote.num_buildings %> building(s)</td><td>$<%= PRICING.digital_signage.usd.toLocaleString() %>/building</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_buildings * PRICING.digital_signage.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <% if (quote.include_visitor_mgmt) { %>
        <tr><td>Visitor Management</td><td><%= quote.num_buildings %> building(s)</td><td>$<%= PRICING.visitor_mgmt.usd.toLocaleString() %>/building</td><td>$<%= (quote.num_buildings * PRICING.visitor_mgmt.usd).toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% } %>
        <tr class="total-row"><td colspan="3">Subtotal</td><td>$<%= quote.subtotal.toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <% if (quote.discount_pct > 0) { %>
        <tr class="discount-row" style="background:#eef7f0;">
          <td colspan="3">
            <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px;">
              <span class="discount-badge"><%= (quote.discount_pct * 100) %>% OFF</span>
              Volume Discount — You're Saving $<%= quote.discount_amount.toLocaleString() %>
            </div>
          </td>
          <td style="color:#1a8a4a; font-weight:600;">&#8722;$<%= quote.discount_amount.toLocaleString() %></td>
        </tr>
        <% } %>
        <tr class="grand-row"><td colspan="3">Total Annual Licence <% if (quote.discount_pct > 0) { %><span style="font-weight:normal; text-decoration:line-through; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size:0.9em;">($<%= quote.subtotal.toLocaleString() %>)</span><% } %></td><td>$<%= quote.total_annual.toLocaleString() %> USD</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Setup Fees -->
  <div class="proposal-card">
    <h2>One-Time Setup Fees</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Detail</th><th>Cost (USD)</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Platform Configuration</td><td>Branding, data import, testing</td><td>$<%= quote.setup_config.toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Map Creation</td><td><%= quote.num_floors %> floor map(s) x $1,000</td><td>$<%= quote.setup_maps.toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Integration & Onboarding</td><td>Directory & calendar sync</td><td>$<%= quote.setup_integration.toLocaleString() %></td></tr>
        <tr class="grand-row"><td colspan="2">Total Setup</td><td>$<%= quote.setup_total.toLocaleString() %> USD</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Payment Milestones -->
  <div class="proposal-card">
    <h2>Payment Milestones</h2>
    <div class="milestone-list">
      <div class="milestone">
        <div class="milestone-num">1</div>
        <div><h4>Signing of Contract</h4><p>Annual licence fee upfront + 50% of setup services ($<%= (quote.total_annual + quote.setup_total * 0.5).toLocaleString() %> USD)</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone">
        <div class="milestone-num">2</div>
        <div><h4>Handover for Testing</h4><p>25% of setup services ($<%= (quote.setup_total * 0.25).toLocaleString() %> USD)</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone">
        <div class="milestone-num">3</div>
        <div><h4>Completion of Testing</h4><p>Final 25% of setup services ($<%= (quote.setup_total * 0.25).toLocaleString() %> USD)</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone">
        <div class="milestone-num">4</div>
        <div><h4>Annual Renewal</h4><p>12-month licence renewal at agreed annual rate.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Accept / Signature -->
  <% if (quote.status === 'pending') { %>

  <!-- Early Bird Bonus Callout -->
  <div class="bonus-card">
    <div class="bonus-badge">BONUS OFFER</div>
    <h3>Sign Within 72 Hours & Get:</h3>
    <div class="bonus-grid">
      <div class="bonus-item">
        <div class="bonus-item-icon"><i data-lucide="dollar-sign" style="stroke:white;"></i></div>
        <div class="bonus-item-title">$2,000 Credit</div>
        <div class="bonus-item-desc">Implementation services</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bonus-item">
        <div class="bonus-item-icon"><i data-lucide="zap" style="stroke:white;"></i></div>
        <div class="bonus-item-title">Priority Onboarding</div>
        <div class="bonus-item-desc">Fast-track your deployment</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bonus-item">
        <div class="bonus-item-icon"><i data-lucide="graduation-cap" style="stroke:white;"></i></div>
        <div class="bonus-item-title">Campus Training</div>
        <div class="bonus-item-desc">Free admin training sessions</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bonus-timer"><span id="bonusTimer" style="font-weight:600;"></span> remaining to claim this offer</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Limited Spots Warning -->
  <div class="warning-callout">
    <i data-lucide="alert-triangle" style="width:24px; height:24px; stroke:#d4a017; flex-shrink:0;"></i>
    <div class="warning-callout-text">
      <strong>Limited Implementation Slots:</strong> Only <strong>3 spots remaining</strong> for next semester deployment. Reserve yours by accepting today.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="proposal-card accept-section" id="acceptSection">
    <h2>Accept This Proposal</h2>
    <p>By signing below, you confirm acceptance of the PlaceOS CampusOS proposal as detailed above.</p>

    <!-- Guarantee Badge -->
    <div class="guarantee-card">
      <h3>90-Day Satisfaction Guarantee</h3>
      <p>If PlaceOS doesn't meet your expectations within the first 90 days, we'll refund your annual licence fee — no questions asked. You have nothing to lose.</p>
      <div class="guarantee-footer">
        Risk-free commitment &middot; Industry-leading platform &middot; Dedicated support team
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="terms-section">
      <div class="terms-header">
        <strong>PlaceOS Terms of Use</strong>
        <div class="terms-actions">
          <button type="button" class="terms-toggle-btn" id="termsToggle">
            <i data-lucide="file-text" style="width:16px; height:16px;"></i>
            View Terms
          </button>
          <a href="/PlaceOS-Terms-of-Use.pdf" download class="terms-download-btn">
            <i data-lucide="download" style="width:16px; height:16px;"></i>
            Download PDF
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="terms-scroll-box" id="termsContent" style="display:none;">
        <h3>Place Technology Group Pte. Ltd. — Terms of Use</h3>
        <h4>PlaceOS One Software as a Service Agreement</h4>

        <p><strong>Important Disclosures</strong></p>
        <p>Our full terms and conditions are set out below. However, before you place an order for our Services, we want to highlight some important points:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Subscription service:</strong> Our Services are provided on a subscription basis. By placing an order, accepting a quote, or otherwise signing up for the Services, you agree to purchase the Services on an ongoing subscription basis for the applicable minimum term set out in your Account, Order, Accepted Quote, or otherwise agreed with us. Your subscription will automatically renew unless terminated in accordance with clause 16.</li>
          <li><strong>Price changes:</strong> We may change our prices from time to time. If we do so, we will give you at least 30 days' prior notice. The new Price will apply from the start of your next billing cycle after that notice period. If you do not agree to the new Price, you may terminate this Agreement in accordance with these terms before the new Price takes effect.</li>
          <li><strong>Changes to these Terms:</strong> We may amend these Terms from time to time in accordance with clause 19.1. If we do so, we will notify you by publishing the updated Terms on our Site, through your Account, or by email.</li>
          <li><strong>Limitation of liability:</strong> To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any loss of or damage to property, personal injury, delay, failure in providing the Services, or breach of these Terms or any law, to the extent caused or contributed to by an event beyond our reasonable control, a third party, or any act or omission of you, your Personnel, Authorised Users or related parties.</li>
          <li><strong>Consumer law:</strong> Nothing in these Terms limits or excludes any rights you may have under applicable consumer protection laws that cannot lawfully be excluded.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>1. Introduction</h4>
        <p>PlaceOS One Software as a Service is a hosted workplace experience solution that enables customers to access and use workplace management features and related services on a subscription basis.</p>

        <h4>2. Definition and interpretation</h4>
        <p>The definitions and rules of interpretation that apply to this Agreement are set out in clause 20.</p>

        <h4>3. Parties and agreement</h4>
        <p>This Agreement is between you, being the customer acquiring the Services (referred to in this Agreement as <strong>you</strong> or <strong>your</strong>), and <strong>Place Technology Group Pte Ltd</strong> (Registration Number 202021470H), including its successors and permitted assigns (referred to in this Agreement as <strong>we</strong>, <strong>us</strong> or <strong>our</strong>). Each party is a <strong>Party</strong> and together they are the <strong>Parties</strong>.</p>
        <p>This Agreement governs the supply of the Services by us to you. Please read this Agreement carefully. If you have any questions, please contact us before accepting this Agreement or using the Services.</p>

        <h4>4. Services</h4>
        <p>You may request, order or subscribe for the Services through our Site, an Accepted Quote, an Order, your Account, a statement of work, or as otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties.</p>
        <p>We will provide the Services, either ourselves or through our Personnel, in accordance with this Agreement.</p>

        <h4>5. Acceptance</h4>
        <p><strong>5.1. Acceptance</strong></p>
        <p>You accept this Agreement, and a binding agreement is formed between the Parties, when you first do any of the following:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>sign or otherwise accept an Order, quote, proposal, statement of work, or other document that references this Agreement;</li>
          <li>provide us with a purchase order in response to our quotation or proposal;</li>
          <li>pay any invoice issued by us for the Services;</li>
          <li>Click a box, button or similar mechanism on the Site or through your Account indicating your acceptance of this Agreement or an Accepted Quote; or</li>
          <li>otherwise access or use the Services after being given notice of this Agreement.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>5.2. Acceptance on behalf of an entity</strong></p>
        <p>If you accept this Agreement on behalf of a company, employer, organisation, government body or other legal entity (<strong>Entity</strong>), then "you" and "your" refer to that Entity, and you represent and warrant that you are authorised to bind that Entity to this Agreement.</p>
        <p><strong>5.3. Term</strong></p>
        <p>This Agreement commences on the date you accept it in accordance with clause 5.1 and continues for the subscription term set out in your Account, Order, Accepted Quote, or otherwise agreed between the Parties, and then renews automatically for successive billing cycles unless terminated in accordance with clause 16.</p>
        <p><strong>5.4. Account Creation</strong></p>
        <p>We may create an account for you to enable you and your Authorised Users to access and use the Services (<strong>Account</strong>). You must ensure that all information you provide to us, or that we request from you in connection with creating or maintaining your Account, is complete, accurate and up to date.</p>
        <p><strong>5.5. Account Owner</strong></p>
        <p>You are responsible for your Account and remain the Account owner unless and until we approve a transfer of the Account to another person or entity.</p>
        <p><strong>5.6. Account credentials and Authorised Users</strong></p>
        <p>We may provide you, or enable you to create, Account credentials such as usernames and passwords. You must keep all Account credentials secure and confidential. You are responsible for all activity carried out through your Account, including by your Authorised Users, and ensuring that your Authorised Users comply with this Agreement.</p>

        <h4>6. Licence and restrictions on use</h4>
        <p><strong>6.1. Licence</strong></p>
        <p>Subject to your compliance with this Agreement, including payment of all applicable Fees, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable (except as expressly permitted under this Agreement), revocable licence to access and use the Services during the Term solely for your internal business purposes and in accordance with this Agreement (<strong>Licence</strong>).</p>
        <p><strong>6.2. Licence Restrictions</strong></p>
        <p>You must not, and must ensure that your Authorised Users do not, access or use the Services except as permitted by this Agreement. You must not, and must not permit any other person to:</p>
        <p>(a) use the Services in any way that breaches any applicable Laws or infringes the rights of any person, including Intellectual Property Rights;<br>
        (b) use the Services to store, transmit, publish or communicate material that is unlawful, defamatory, offensive, abusive, indecent, menacing, misleading or otherwise inappropriate;<br>
        (c) use the Services in any way that damages, disrupts, interferes with or interrupts the Services or any related systems or networks;<br>
        (d) introduce into the Services or our systems any malicious code, virus, worm, Trojan horse, malware, spyware or other harmful or disruptive code;<br>
        (e) disclose Account credentials to unauthorised persons or allow any person other than Authorised Users to access or use the Services through your Account;<br>
        (f) use the Services to attempt to gain unauthorised access to any system, network, account or data;<br>
        (g) use any automated means, program, script, bot, scraper, crawler, command or process to interfere with, disable, overburden or impair the Services or any person's use of the Services;<br>
        (h) use the Services to send spam, harassing communications, fraudulent communications, or messages that breach any person's privacy or facilitate identity theft, phishing or other deceptive conduct;<br>
        (i) circumvent or attempt to circumvent any authentication, access control, security measure, usage limit or technical restriction of the Services or any related network, account or host;<br>
        (j) copy, modify, adapt, translate, reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, create derivative works from, or otherwise attempt to discover the source code, object code or underlying structure, ideas or algorithms of the Services, except to the extent such restriction is prohibited by law; or<br>
        (k) use the Services for the benefit of any third party, including to provide outsourcing, service bureau, timesharing, rental, resale, sub-licensing or other similar services, except as expressly permitted under this Agreement.</p>
        <p><strong>6.3. Required licences, approvals and consents</strong></p>
        <p>You must promptly obtain and maintain all licences, approvals, permissions and consents required for us to provide the Services to you, including any third-party consents required for integrations, data access, implementation, deployment or use of the Services in your environment.</p>

        <h4>7. Authorised Licence</h4>
        <p><strong>7.1. Authorised Licence</strong></p>
        <p>If specified on the Site, in your Account, in an Order, Accepted Quote, statement of work, or otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties, your Licence to access and use the Services is limited by the applicable usage metrics for your subscription, which may include the number of desks, rooms, floors, buildings, square metres (SQM), square feet (SQF), users, modules, locations, or any other agreed usage metric (<strong>Authorised Licence Metrics</strong>).</p>
        <p><strong>7.2. Increasing on Authorised Licence Metrics</strong></p>
        <p>You may request an increase to your Authorised Licence Metrics at any time by email, through your Account, or through any other method we make available. Any approved increase may result in an adjustment to the Fees.</p>

        <h4>8. Third-Party Inputs and interoperability</h4>
        <p>You acknowledge and agree that the availability, performance and functionality of the Services may depend on, interact with, or be affected by third-party products, services, systems, integrations, networks, suppliers, subcontractors, or other external inputs (Third-Party Inputs). We are not responsible for, and will have no Liability for, any delay, failure, defect, unavailability, error, security issue, loss or breach arising from or caused by any Third-Party Inputs.</p>

        <h4>9. Setup Services, Data Load, Hosting and Variations</h4>
        <p>If applicable, we will provide any Setup Services, implementation services, configuration services, onboarding services, hosting services and Data Load services as set out on the Site, in your Account, in an Order, Accepted Quote, statement of work, or as otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties.</p>

        <h4>10. Support Services</h4>
        <p>We will provide the support services set out in this clause 10 as part of your subscription for the Services, to the extent included in your subscription plan, Account, Order, Accepted Quote, or as otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties.</p>
        <p><strong>10.5. Availability:</strong> Subject to this Agreement, we will use reasonable efforts to make the Services available at least 99.5% of the Service Hours in each calendar month.</p>

        <h4>11. Privacy</h4>
        <p>To the extent that we process Customer Data that contains Personal Data, we will do so in accordance with applicable Privacy Laws, this Agreement, and any applicable Data Processing Addendum.</p>

        <h4>12. Fees and payment</h4>
        <p>You must pay the Fees and all other amounts payable under this Agreement in accordance with this Agreement, your Account, Order, Accepted Quote, statement of work, or as otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties. Unless otherwise agreed in writing, we may invoice you in advance for each billing cycle. You must pay each invoice within 30 days of the invoice date.</p>

        <h4>13. Taxes</h4>
        <p>Unless expressly stated otherwise, all Fees and other amounts payable under this Agreement are exclusive of GST, VAT, sales tax, withholding tax and any similar taxes, duties or levies.</p>

        <h4>14. Intellectual Property Rights</h4>
        <p>All Intellectual Property Rights in the Services, Software, Site, documentation, materials and all other works, developments, modifications, adaptations, enhancements, configurations, customisations, derivative works, tools, processes, know-how and other materials created, developed, adapted, modified or supplied by us or our Personnel, whether independently or in connection with this Agreement, remain vested in and are owned by us or our licensors.</p>

        <h4>15. Liability exclusions, indemnity and acknowledgements</h4>
        <p><strong>15.1. Liability cap:</strong> To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total aggregate Liability arising out of or in connection with this Agreement is limited to the total Fees paid or payable by you to us under this Agreement in the 12 months immediately preceding the event giving rise to the Liability.</p>
        <p><strong>15.2. Exclusion of Consequential Loss:</strong> To the maximum extent permitted by law, neither Party is liable to the other for any Consequential Loss arising out of or in connection with this Agreement.</p>

        <h4>16. Termination</h4>
        <p><strong>16.1. Mutual Termination:</strong> The Parties may terminate this Agreement at any time by written agreement signed by both Parties.</p>
        <p><strong>16.2. Termination without cause:</strong> Either Party may terminate this Agreement for convenience by giving the other Party at least 30 days' prior written notice.</p>
        <p><strong>16.3. Termination for cause:</strong> Either Party may terminate this Agreement, with written notice, if the other Party materially breaches this Agreement and fails to remedy the breach within 20 Business Days after receiving written notice.</p>
        <p><strong>16.4. Effect of termination:</strong> On termination or expiry, your right to access and use the Services immediately ceases; all Fees and other amounts accrued or payable become immediately due; all amounts paid are non-refundable except as required by law; and each Party must promptly return, delete or destroy the other Party's Confidential Information.</p>
        <p><strong>16.5. Access to and removal of Customer Data:</strong> Following termination or expiry, you may, for up to 3 months, access the Services solely for the purpose of retrieving or exporting your Customer Data, provided that you have paid all Fees.</p>

